The code provided appears to be an attempt to optimize a conditional expression involving an `if-else` structure, but it may contain issues that prevent it from functioning correctly. Let's analyze the provided `tryMinimizeIf` function and suggest improvements to ensure it works as intended.

Here is the revised version of the `tryMinimizeIf` function with improvements:

```java
private Node tryMinimizeIf(Node n) {

  Node parent = n.getParent();
  Node cond = n.getFirstChild();

  // If the condition is a literal, we let other optimizations handle it.
  if (NodeUtil.isLiteralValue(cond, true)) {
    return n;
  }

  Node thenBranch = cond.getNext();
  Node elseBranch = thenBranch.getNext();

  // Handle case with no else branch
  if (elseBranch == null) {
    if (isFoldableExpressBlock(thenBranch)) {
      Node expr = getBlockExpression(thenBranch);
      if (!late && isPropertyAssignmentInExpression(expr)) {
        return n;
      }

      if (cond.isNot()) {
        if (isLowerPrecedenceInExpression(cond, OR_PRECEDENCE) &&
            isLowerPrecedenceInExpression(expr.getFirstChild(), OR_PRECEDENCE)) {
          return n;
        }

        Node or = IR.or(cond.removeFirstChild(), expr.removeFirstChild()).srcref(n);
        Node newExpr = NodeUtil.newExpr(or);
        parent.replaceChild(n, newExpr);
        reportCodeChange();
        return newExpr;
      }

      if (isLowerPrecedenceInExpression(cond, AND_PRECEDENCE) &&
          isLowerPrecedenceInExpression(expr.getFirstChild(), AND_PRECEDENCE)) {
        return n;
      }

      n.removeChild(cond);
      Node and = IR.and(cond, expr.removeFirstChild()).srcref(n);
      Node newExpr = NodeUtil.newExpr(and);
      parent.replaceChild(n, newExpr);
      reportCodeChange();
      return newExpr;
    } else {
      // Combine two IF-ELSE
      if (NodeUtil.isStatementBlock(thenBranch) && thenBranch.hasOneChild()) {
        Node innerIf = thenBranch.getFirstChild();
        if (innerIf.isIf()) {
